    {
      "type": "explanation",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "title",
          "value": "Numbers 1 to 5"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Numbers in Cantonese are straightforward, but there is one very important rule for the number '2'. Let's start with the first five digits."
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "一",
          "romanization": "jat1",
          "translation": "One"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "二",
          "romanization": "ji6",
          "translation": "Two (for counting)"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "三",
          "romanization": "saam1",
          "translation": "Three"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "四",
          "romanization": "sei3",
          "translation": "Four"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "五",
          "romanization": "ng5",
          "translation": "Five"
        },
        {
          "type": "title",
          "value": "The Rule of Two"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "When you are just counting (1, 2, 3...) or saying a phone number, use <strong>二</strong> (ji6). However, when you are counting <em>objects</em> (two people, two cats, two books), you must use <strong>兩</strong> (loeng5)."
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "兩",
          "romanization": "loeng5",
          "translation": "Two (of something / a couple)"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "reading",
      "exerciseId": "4.1.2"
    },
    {
      "type": "unscramble",
      "exerciseId": "4.1.3"
    },
    {
      "type": "explanation",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "title",
          "value": "Numbers 6 to 10"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Now let's complete the set from six to ten."
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "六",
          "romanization": "luk6",
          "translation": "Six"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "七",
          "romanization": "cat1",
          "translation": "Seven"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "八",
          "romanization": "baat3",
          "translation": "Eight"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "九",
          "romanization": "gau2",
          "translation": "Nine"
        },
        {
          "type": "example",
          "cantonese": "十",
          "romanization": "sap6",
          "translation": "Ten"
        }
      ]
    },
